<!-- post # 17 --><font color="#FF0000">DEPARTURES AND ARRIVALS</font><br><tt>Tue Nov 12 22:03:41 US/Eastern 1996</tt><p>My first unit participated in the first retaliatory raids on North Vietnam (Gulf of Tonkin Incident, August 2-5, 1964).  We proudly flew a combat banner 1080 feet long and were greeted by an exuberant crowd in San Diego who showered us with love and support.<br><br>Approximately eight years later, with a different detachment and mission supporting troops in Vietnam, we flew back in a chartered U.S. air carrier and were greeted with jeers and spit and other objects as our bus took us away.<br><br>Same war, probably some of the same people.  Who would go back after that?<br><br><p><code>-- jtpankey@htc.net  (Jim Pankey) </code><p>